### 1. Hierarchical Orchestration

**Description**:  
Hierarchical orchestration involves organizing agents into a structured hierarchy where higher-level agents manage lower-level agents, enabling scalable and modular orchestration.

**Implementation Notes**:  
Implementing hierarchical orchestration requires careful design of communication protocols and task delegation mechanisms to ensure efficient coordination.

